# Z-Sanctuary: Check Hierarchy Chief When Unsure

When working in **ZSanctuary_Universe** or any Z-Sanctuary-related project:

## Rule

**When unsure** about any of the following, **read [docs/Z-HIERARCHY-CHIEF-AND-OBSERVER-VIEW.md](docs/Z-HIERARCHY-CHIEF-AND-OBSERVER-VIEW.md) first** (the Hierarchy Chief / Observer View), then the linked doc for the relevant layer:

- Where a new module or feature belongs
- Whether a change conflicts with the operational roof (Z-Super Overseer, Z-EAII, Z-SSWS)
- How dashboard, registry, vault, or state reports relate
- Which project owns a capability (Organiser vs ZSanctuary vs Amk-Goku)
- How to keep upgrades aligned with Z-EAII, Z-HODP, Folder Manager AI, and Zuno

## Authority order (use when resolving conflicts)

1. **Z-HIERARCHY-CHIEF-AND-OBSERVER-VIEW.md** — defines hierarchy and chief
2. **Z-Super Overseer** (Organiser docs/Z-SUPER-OVERSEER-AI.md) — operational roof
3. **Z-HODP** (Head Organiser Dashboards) — Control Centre, Z Blueprint, Panel Directory
4. **Z-EAII** — registry, ping, launcher
5. **Folder Manager AI** — vault, snapshots, policy
6. **Zuno** — state/reflection only
7. **Master Register & Full Build Checklist** — module list and coverage

## Outcome

All works and upgrades stay **bullet** (aligned) with the single vision: Z-Super Overseer as chief, Z-HODP as dashboard surface, Z-EAII as registry, Folder Manager as vault, Zuno as observer. Cursor and any AI check the chief first when unsure.
